## 1CCodeChecker Tools (1С:Напарник, 1c-code-check-mcp)

**11 tools** for code analysis, review, modification, and documentation access.

### Code Analysis & Modification

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **check_1c_code** | Technical check: syntax, logic, performance | After writing code — find bugs and performance issues |
| **review_1c_code** | Code review: style, ITS standards, naming, structure | After writing code — ensure standards compliance |
| **rewrite_1c_code** | AI rewrites code with improvements (optional `goal`: `optimize`, `readability`, `error handling`) | When code needs significant improvement |
| **modify_1c_code** | Modify or generate code by explicit instruction | Apply targeted changes, fix specific bugs, add features |
| **ask_1c_ai** | Free-form question to 1С:Напарник (preserves dialog context) | Architecture questions, concept explanations, advice |

### Documentation & Knowledge Base

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **search_1c_documentation** | Search platform docs for specific version (e.g. `v8.3.25`) | Version-specific method signatures, platform features |
| **onec_help** | Search platform docs (latest version) | Quick lookup of platform features, methods, types |
| **its_help** | Search ITS knowledge base (standards, methodologies) | Find ITS standards, best practices. **Returns document IDs → use `fetch_its`** |
| **fetch_its** | Read full ITS document by ID | **Always use after `its_help`** to read found articles. Special IDs: `root`, `v8std` |
| **diff_1c_documentation_versions** | Compare docs between platform versions | Check changes between versions (e.g. `v8.3.25` → `v8.5.1`) |
| **config_help** | Search docs for specific configs (ERP, БП, ЗУП, УТ) | Config-specific business logic, object descriptions |

> **Key workflow**: `its_help` → get document IDs → `fetch_its` with each ID to read full content. Never ignore ITS article references.

## Tool Usage by Task

### Writing New Code
1. **templatesearch** — find similar implementations
2. **get_object_dossier** — understand target metadata object structure, forms, dependencies, and code in one call
3. **search_code** → **codesearch** — check existing patterns in configuration
4. **search_function** — find existing procedures/functions by name to reuse
5. **get_module_structure** — understand the module you're about to edit
6. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — verify metadata structure and attribute types
7. **bsl_scope_members** — discover available methods/properties for the context you're working with
8. **docinfo** — verify built-in functions/methods by exact name; **docsearch** — search by description
9. **ssl_search** — find reusable SSL functions
10. **syntaxcheck** — verify syntax after writing
11. **check_1c_code** — find logic and performance issues
12. **review_1c_code** — verify style and standards compliance

### Code Review
1. **search_code** → **codesearch** — verify pattern compliance
2. **trace_impact** → **graph_dependencies** — impact analysis of the code being reviewed
3. **trace_call_chain** → **get_method_call_hierarchy** — trace BSL call chains, find all callers/callees
5. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — check correct metadata usage
6. **docinfo** — verify method/property existence by exact name; **docsearch** — search by description
7. **review_1c_code** — check style and ITS standards compliance
8. **check_1c_code** — find bugs and performance issues
9. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — verify against ITS standards

### Architecture Design
1. **get_object_dossier** — comprehensive passport of key metadata objects (structure, forms, deps, code, roles)
2. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — understand existing metadata structure
3. **trace_impact** → **graph_dependencies** — dependency mapping across USED_IN, DO_MOVEMENTS_IN, CALLS
4. **find_objects_using_object** — find all objects referencing a given object
5. **search_code** → **codesearch** — find existing patterns
6. **trace_call_chain** → **get_method_call_hierarchy** — understand code coupling and call chains
8. **templatesearch** — find architectural templates
9. **ask_1c_ai** — get architectural advice from 1С:Напарник
10. **config_help** — understand how specific configurations implement patterns

### Error Fixing
1. **syntaxcheck** — identify syntax errors
2. **check_1c_code** — identify logic and performance problems
3. **search_function** — find the problematic procedure/function
4. **search_code** → **codesearch** — find related code patterns (use `detail_level="L0"` for full code of a specific routine)
5. **get_module_structure** — understand module context around the error
6. **trace_call_chain** → **get_method_call_hierarchy** — trace how the error propagates through call chains
7. **docinfo** — verify correct function/method names; **docsearch** — search if unsure
8. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — verify metadata object names and attributes
9. **modify_1c_code** — apply targeted fixes via AI

### Performance Optimization
1. **search_code** → **codesearch** — find slow patterns (use `semantic` search for "медленный запрос", "цикл по выборке" etc.)
2. **trace_call_chain** → **get_method_call_hierarchy** — identify hot call paths
3. **trace_impact** → **graph_dependencies** — find objects causing cascading performance issues (use `relationship_types=["CALLS"]` for code-only paths)
6. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — check indexes and metadata structure
7. **check_1c_code** — analyze performance issues
8. **rewrite_1c_code** — get AI-optimized code (with `goal: optimize`)
9. **templatesearch** — find optimized patterns
10. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — find ITS performance standards

### Refactoring
1. **get_object_dossier** — comprehensive passport of the object being refactored
2. **trace_impact** → **graph_dependencies** (`direction="downstream"`) — analyze what breaks if object changes
3. **trace_call_chain** → **get_method_call_hierarchy** (`direction="callers"`) — find all callers of refactored routines
4. **find_objects_using_object** / **find_usages_of_object** — find all type references before renaming/removing
5. **search_code** → **codesearch** — find all code patterns related to the refactored object
6. **search_code** (`detail_level="L3"`, high `top_k`) → **codesearch** — verify no remaining references after refactoring
7. **check_1c_code** + **review_1c_code** — validate refactored code

### Generating/Modifying Metadata XML
1. **metadatasearch** (`names_only=true`) — find similar metadata objects as examples
2. **get_xsd_schema** — get XSD schema for the target metadata type to know expected structure
3. Write/modify XML according to schema and examples
4. **verify_xml** — validate generated XML against XSD; fix errors if any
5. Use **1c-metadata-manage** skill to compile and deploy

### Form Analysis and Generation
1. **search_forms** — find similar existing forms in the configuration
2. **inspect_form_layout** — study the structure of a found similar form (elements, bindings, commands, events)
3. **metadatasearch** (`names_only=true`) — find metadata objects for XML reference
4. **get_xsd_schema**(`"Форма"`) — get XSD schema for form XML structure
5. Generate Form.xml based on examples and schema
6. **verify_xml** — validate the generated Form.xml against XSD
7. Use **1c-metadata-manage** skill (form-manage section) to compile and validate

### Documentation
1. **codesearch** — find code to document
2. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — understand metadata structure
3. **get_module_structure** — get procedure/function list for documentation
4. **docinfo** — get documentation for a specific object/method; **docsearch** — search by description
5. **helpsearch** — find existing help articles
6. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — find and read ITS methodological articles
7. **search_1c_documentation** — find version-specific platform docs

### Comparing Platform Versions
1. **diff_1c_documentation_versions** — see what changed between versions
2. **search_1c_documentation** — search docs for specific version

## Important Rules

1. **Always search before writing** — use `templatesearch` and `codesearch` / `search_code` first
2. **Verify against documentation** — use `docinfo` for known names, `docsearch` for description-based search
3. **Check metadata exists** — use `metadatasearch` + `get_metadata_details` before using objects; use `get_object_dossier` for a complete structural passport
4. **Use structural tools** — `search_function`, `get_module_structure`, `get_method_call_hierarchy` for code navigation instead of manual grep
5. **Validate generated XML** — always use `get_xsd_schema` before writing XML and `verify_xml` after
6. **Limit syntaxcheck** — maximum 3 times per cycle, then move on
7. **Grep/rg only as absolute last resort** — always exhaust MCP tools first: `search_code` → `codesearch` → only then Grep. For metadata: `search_metadata` / `search_metadata_by_description` / `find_objects_using_object` / `find_usages_of_object` / `resolve_qualified_name` → `metadatasearch` → only then Grep
9. **Always follow up `its_help` with `fetch_its`** — read full ITS article content by ID
10. **Use 1CCodeChecker tools actively** — `check_1c_code` and `review_1c_code` after every code change
11. **Use `get_object_dossier` first** — when you need to understand any metadata object before deeper analysis. One call replaces multiple separate queries
12. **Use `trace_impact` → `graph_dependencies` for impact analysis** — before refactoring, use recursive multi-level impact analysis; fall back to flat dependency list if graph unavailable
13. **Use `trace_call_chain` for call graph analysis** — trace BSL call chains with depth control before modifying routines
13. **Tool priority: graph → code-metadata → Grep** — always prefer `1c-graph-metadata-mcp` tools; fall back to `1c-code-metadata-mcp` if graph is unavailable or found nothing; use Grep only as absolute last resort
